{"title_page": "VMware ThinApp", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{Notability|Products|date=December 2015}}\n{{Advert|date=December 2015}}\n}}\n\n{{Infobox software\n| name = VMware ThinApp\n| logo = VMware ThinApp v4.0 icon.png\n| screenshot = \n| caption = \n| collapsible = \n| author = Jitit Inc.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://communities.vmware.com/blogs/rameshgeddam/2010/09/22/vmware-thinapp-history-and-basic-working-nature|title=vFILTERS: VMware Thinapp history and basic work... - VMware Communities|work=vmware.com}}</ref>\n| developer = [[VMware]]\n| released = \n| latest release version = 5.2.7\n| latest release date = {{Start date and age|2020|03|31}}<ref>{{Cite web\n  |url = https://docs.vmware.com/en/VMware-ThinApp/5.2.7/rn/VMware-ThinApp-527-Release-Notes.html\n  |title = VMware ThinApp 5.2.7 Release Notes\n  |work = VMware ThinApp 5.2.7 Release Notes\n  |publisher = VMware, Inc\n  |date = March 29, 2020\n  |accessdate = April 21, 2020\n }}</ref>\n| latest preview version = \n| latest preview date = \n| programming language = \n| operating system = [[Windows Vista]] and later<br/>[[Windows Server 2008]] and later (Windows XP and 2k3 supported  by 5.2.3 and old version)\n| platform = \n| size = 85.5&nbsp;[[Megabytes|MB]]\n| language = \n| genre = [[Application virtualization]]<br />[[Portable application creator]]\n| license = [[Shareware]]\n| website = {{URL|http://www.vmware.com/products/thinapp}}\n}}\n\n'''VMware ThinApp''' (formerly ''Thinstall'') is an [[application virtualization]] and [[portable application creator]] suite by [[VMware]] that can package conventional applications<ref name=man51 /> so that they become [[portable application]]s. According to VMware, the product has a success rate of about 90\u201395 % in packaging applications.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.vmware.com/thinapp/2009/12/top-10-questions-on-thinapp.html|title=Top 10 Questions on ThinApp|work=vmware.com}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nThinApp (previously known as Thinstall) was originally developed by Jitit Inc. and was acquired by [[VMware]] on January 15, 2008.<ref>{{cite press release|url=http://www.vmware.com/company/news/releases/thinstall.html|title=VMware to Expand Desktop Virtualization Solution with Acquisition of Thinstall|date=January 15, 2008|accessdate=2008-06-11|publisher=[[VMware]]}}</ref> VMware later used the code name ''VMware Project North Star'' while the product was in [[Software release life cycle#Beta|beta]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://communities.vmware.com/community/beta/northstar|title=VMware ThinApp (Project North Star/Thinstall) Release Candidate|date=June 10, 2008|accessdate=2008-06-11|publisher=[[VMware]]}}</ref> On June 10, 2008, VMware announced that the final name for the product was going to be ''VMware ThinApp''.<ref>{{cite press release|url=http://www.vmware.com/company/news/releases/thinapp_4.html|title=VMware Launches ThinApp 4.0 to Run Virtually Any Application on Any Windows Operating System without Conflict by raju|date=June 10, 2008|accessdate=2008-06-11|publisher=[[VMware]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080612135439/http://www.vmware.com/company/news/releases/thinapp_4.html|archive-date=June 12, 2008|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The trial version of ''Thinstall'' was initially available only to corporations,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinstall.com/products/virtualization_suite_dl.php |title=VMware ThinApp Application Virtualization Platform: IT Management Solutions |publisher=Thinstall.com |accessdate=2009-10-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090312070738/http://www.thinstall.com/products/virtualization_suite_dl.php |archive-date=2009-03-12 |url-status=dead }}</ref> then VMware offered a public [[Shareware#Trialware|trial version]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vmware.com/go/trythinapp|title=Evaluate VMware ThinApp|publisher=[[VMware]]|accessdate=2008-08-09}}</ref> Now, ThinApp is only available with the Horizon suite of products.\n\n== Technology ==\nVMware ThinApp is an [[application virtualization]] solution.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vmware.com/pdf/thinapp_intro.pdf|title=Introduction to VMware ThinApp|date=2008-06-26|accessdate=2008-08-05|publisher=[[VMware]]}}</ref> ThinApp is able to execute applications without them being installed in the traditional sense by virtualizing resources such as environment variables, files and [[Windows Registry]] keys. The virtual environment presented to the client is a merged view of the underlying physical and virtual resources, thereby allowing the virtualization layer to fool the application into thinking that it is running as if it were fully installed. ThinApp does not have any pre-installed components and does not require the installation of device drivers allowing applications to run from USB flash drives or network shares without ever requiring Administrator rights. ThinApp converts standard application installers such as .msi files into self-contained EXE files which includes everything required to run. Also it is able to scan a system before and after an application's installation and create a portable executable based upon changes made to the systems files and registry. Unlike self-extracting ZIP files, ThinApp does not extract files to disk or require system registry changes in order to run applications. ThinApp supports Windows XP and later, as well as Windows Server 2003 and later. ThinApp supports all released Windows systems from Windows NT4, 2000, XP (64/32), Vista (64/32),  Server 2003, Server 2008 (64), Server 2008 R2 (64), Windows 7 (64/32), Windows 8/8.1 (64/32, but not RT), and Windows 2012.<reF name=man51>{{cite book |url=https://www.vmware.com/pdf/thinapp51_manual.pdf |title=ThinApp User\u2019s Guide: ThinApp 5.1 |publisher=[[VMware]] |date=10 December 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Editions==\n{{update|section|date=December 2015}}\nThe most \"basic\" version of ThinApp is \"VMware ThinApp Starter Edition\", offered for free with any purchase of [[VMware Workstation]],<ref name=\"vmware.com\">http://www.vmware.com/products/workstation/thinapp-starter-edition.html</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.vmware.com/workstation/2010/11/buy-vmware-workstation-7-get-vmware-thinapp-starter-edition-for-free.html|title=Buy VMware Workstation 7, Get VMware ThinApp Starter Edition For Free!|work=vmware.com}}</ref> while the most \"advanced\" version is \"VMware ThinApp Enterprise Edition\", which adds support for ''AppSync updating'', ''Active Directory integration'' and allows usage by multiple users (both for the ''ThinApp Packager'' and ''ThinApp Client'').<ref name=\"vmware.com\"/>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Microsoft App-V]]\n* [[Turbo (software)]]\n* [[Software appliance]]\n* [[Windows To Go]]\n* [[Sandboxie]]\n* [[Portable application creators]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|http://www.vmware.com/products/thinapp/}}\n\n[[Category:VMware|ThinApp]]\n[[Category:Virtualization software]]\n[[Category:Utilities for Windows]]\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{Notability|Products|date=December 2015}}\n{{Advert|date=December 2015}}\n}}\n\n{{Infobox software\n| name = VMware ThinApp\n| logo = VMware ThinApp v4.0 icon.png\n| screenshot = \n| caption = \n| collapsible = \n| author = Jitit Inc.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://communities.vmware.com/blogs/rameshgeddam/2010/09/22/vmware-thinapp-history-and-basic-working-nature|title=vFILTERS: VMware Thinapp history and basic work... - VMware Communities|work=vmware.com}}</ref>\n| developer = [[VMware]]\n| released = \n| latest release version = 5.2.6\n| latest release date = {{Start date and age|2019|09|12}}<ref>{{Cite web\n  |url = https://docs.vmware.com/en/VMware-ThinApp/5.2.6/rn/VMware-ThinApp-526-Release-Notes.html\n  |title = VMware ThinApp 5.2.6 Release Notes\n  |work = VMware ThinApp 5.2.6 Release Notes\n  |publisher = VMware, Inc\n  |date = September 12, 2019\n  |accessdate = September 12, 2019\n }}</ref>\n| latest preview version = \n| latest preview date = \n| programming language = \n| operating system = [[Windows Vista]] and later<br/>[[Windows Server 2008]] and later (Windows XP and 2k3 supported  by 5.2.3 and old version)\n| platform = \n| size = 85.5&nbsp;[[Megabytes|MB]]\n| language = \n| genre = [[Application virtualization]]<br />[[Portable application creator]]\n| license = [[Shareware]]\n| website = {{URL|http://www.vmware.com/products/thinapp}}\n}}\n\n'''VMware ThinApp''' (formerly ''Thinstall'') is an [[application virtualization]] and [[portable application creator]] suite by [[VMware]] that can package conventional applications<ref name=man51 /> so that they become [[portable application]]s. According to VMware, the product has a success rate of about 90\u201395 % in packaging applications.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.vmware.com/thinapp/2009/12/top-10-questions-on-thinapp.html|title=Top 10 Questions on ThinApp|work=vmware.com}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nThinApp (previously known as Thinstall) was originally developed by Jitit Inc. and was acquired by [[VMware]] on January 15, 2008.<ref>{{cite press release|url=http://www.vmware.com/company/news/releases/thinstall.html|title=VMware to Expand Desktop Virtualization Solution with Acquisition of Thinstall|date=January 15, 2008|accessdate=2008-06-11|publisher=[[VMware]]}}</ref> VMware later used the code name ''VMware Project North Star'' while the product was in [[Software release life cycle#Beta|beta]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://communities.vmware.com/community/beta/northstar|title=VMware ThinApp (Project North Star/Thinstall) Release Candidate|date=June 10, 2008|accessdate=2008-06-11|publisher=[[VMware]]}}</ref> On June 10, 2008, VMware announced that the final name for the product was going to be ''VMware ThinApp''.<ref>{{cite press release|url=http://www.vmware.com/company/news/releases/thinapp_4.html|title=VMware Launches ThinApp 4.0 to Run Virtually Any Application on Any Windows Operating System without Conflict by raju|date=June 10, 2008|accessdate=2008-06-11|publisher=[[VMware]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080612135439/http://www.vmware.com/company/news/releases/thinapp_4.html|archive-date=June 12, 2008|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The trial version of ''Thinstall'' was initially available only to corporations,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thinstall.com/products/virtualization_suite_dl.php |title=VMware ThinApp Application Virtualization Platform: IT Management Solutions |publisher=Thinstall.com |accessdate=2009-10-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090312070738/http://www.thinstall.com/products/virtualization_suite_dl.php |archive-date=2009-03-12 |url-status=dead }}</ref> then VMware offered a public [[Shareware#Trialware|trial version]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vmware.com/go/trythinapp|title=Evaluate VMware ThinApp|publisher=[[VMware]]|accessdate=2008-08-09}}</ref> Now, ThinApp is only available with the Horizon suite of products.\n\n== Technology ==\nVMware ThinApp is an [[application virtualization]] solution.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vmware.com/pdf/thinapp_intro.pdf|title=Introduction to VMware ThinApp|date=2008-06-26|accessdate=2008-08-05|publisher=[[VMware]]}}</ref> ThinApp is able to execute applications without them being installed in the traditional sense by virtualizing resources such as environment variables, files and [[Windows Registry]] keys. The virtual environment presented to the client is a merged view of the underlying physical and virtual resources, thereby allowing the virtualization layer to fool the application into thinking that it is running as if it were fully installed. ThinApp does not have any pre-installed components and does not require the installation of device drivers allowing applications to run from USB flash drives or network shares without ever requiring Administrator rights. ThinApp converts standard application installers such as .msi files into self-contained EXE files which includes everything required to run. Also it is able to scan a system before and after an application's installation and create a portable executable based upon changes made to the systems files and registry. Unlike self-extracting ZIP files, ThinApp does not extract files to disk or require system registry changes in order to run applications. ThinApp supports Windows XP and later, as well as Windows Server 2003 and later. ThinApp supports all released Windows systems from Windows NT4, 2000, XP (64/32), Vista (64/32),  Server 2003, Server 2008 (64), Server 2008 R2 (64), Windows 7 (64/32), Windows 8/8.1 (64/32, but not RT), and Windows 2012.<reF name=man51>{{cite book |url=https://www.vmware.com/pdf/thinapp51_manual.pdf |title=ThinApp User\u2019s Guide: ThinApp 5.1 |publisher=[[VMware]] |date=10 December 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Editions==\n{{update|section|date=December 2015}}\nThe most \"basic\" version of ThinApp is \"VMware ThinApp Starter Edition\", offered for free with any purchase of [[VMware Workstation]],<ref name=\"vmware.com\">http://www.vmware.com/products/workstation/thinapp-starter-edition.html</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.vmware.com/workstation/2010/11/buy-vmware-workstation-7-get-vmware-thinapp-starter-edition-for-free.html|title=Buy VMware Workstation 7, Get VMware ThinApp Starter Edition For Free!|work=vmware.com}}</ref> while the most \"advanced\" version is \"VMware ThinApp Enterprise Edition\", which adds support for ''AppSync updating'', ''Active Directory integration'' and allows usage by multiple users (both for the ''ThinApp Packager'' and ''ThinApp Client'').<ref name=\"vmware.com\"/>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Microsoft App-V]]\n* [[Turbo (software)]]\n* [[Software appliance]]\n* [[Windows To Go]]\n* [[Sandboxie]]\n* [[Portable application creators]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|http://www.vmware.com/products/thinapp/}}\n\n[[Category:VMware|ThinApp]]\n[[Category:Virtualization software]]\n[[Category:Utilities for Windows]]\n", "